{
  "doc_id": "38979",
  "text": "The KMT2A/MLL1 is necessary for regulation of genes with key roles in differentiation and development [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [ [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . It has multiple domains that mediate binding to both proteins and DNA, and allow assembly of the multiprotein complex that regulates gene expression. KMT2A/ MLL1 has a SET domain that, within the complex, confers lysine methyltransferase activity specific for histone H3 lysine 4 (H3K4), and is essential for gene regulation [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] .",
